    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>Il conte di palazzo Amedeo, <rs key="#Missus_regis">inviato</rs> in <rs
                            key="#Geographic_regions">Tuscia</rs> dall’<rs key="#Emperor/king"
                            >imperatore</rs>
                        <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/136">Lamberto</persName>, siede
                        in giudizio <rs key="#Cities">civitate</rs>
                        <placeName ref="#places/2"
                            key="#Cities #Palatia #Viscount #Mother_churches #Bishops"
                            >Florencia</placeName> in <rs key="#Palatia">domum episcopii ipsius
                            civitatis</rs>, in atrio ante <orgName key="#Mother_churches"><rs
                                key="#Mother_churches">basilica</rs> Sancti Ioanni
                        Batista</orgName>, con il marchese Adalberto; assistono, fra gli altri, i
                            <rs key="#Bishops">vescovi</rs>
                        <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/138">Elbungo</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/53" key="#Bishops">Parma</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/290">Lupo</persName> di <placeName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#places/164">Siena</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/139">Odalberto</persName> di <placeName
                            ref="#places/67" key="#Bishops">Luni</placeName>, <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/271">Grasulfo</persName> di Firenze; i
                        giudici imperiali Giovanni, Adalberto e altro Adalberto; i <rs
                            key="#vassusOf">vassalli marchionali</rs>
                        <persName key="#vassusOf" ref="#people/144">Winigildo</persName> del
                            <persName ref="#people/145">fu Furulo</persName>, <persName
                            key="#vassusOf" ref="#people/140">Rodilando</persName>, <persName
                            key="#vassusOf" ref="#people/141">Sichelmo</persName> e <persName
                            key="#vassusOf" ref="#people/142">Ghisalberto</persName>; <persName
                            key="#Viscount" ref="#people/143">Teudicio</persName>
                        <rs key="#Viscount">visconte</rs> ipsius civitatis; gli <rs key="#Scabini"
                            >scabini</rs> ipsius civitatis <persName key="#Scabini"><name
                                ref="Rotarius">Rotari</name></persName> e <persName key="#Scabini"
                                ><name ref="Petrus">Pietro</name></persName>. Si presenta <persName
                            key="#Bishops" ref="#people/213">Pietro</persName>, <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >vescovo</rs> di <placeName ref="#places/4"
                            key="#Cities #Clusae/gates #Mother_churches #Bishops">Lucca</placeName>,
                        con il suo <rs key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities">advocatus</rs>
                        <persName key="#Advocatus_of_other_public_authorities"><name
                                ref="Teudebertus">Teuperto</name></persName>, contestando alle
                        seguenti persone beni che spettano al suo vescovato e che essi tengono
                        nescimus pro qua causa: i fratelli <persName><name ref="Sisemundus"
                                >Sisemundo</name></persName> e <persName><name ref="Offo"
                                >Offo</name></persName> tengono beni a <placeName ref="#places/161"
                            >Valiano</placeName>; <persName ref="#people/146">Adalfridi</persName>
                        la <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di Santa Maria
                            di <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/163"
                            >Fereniano</placeName></orgName> con le sue pertinenze e <rs
                            key="#Manentes">5 manentes</rs> a <placeName key="#Manentes"
                            >Ciciano</placeName>; <persName ref="#people/150"
                            key="#Consortes/shared_possessions">Fraolmi</persName> con i suoi <rs
                            key="#Consortes/shared_possessions">consortes</rs> beni prope <rs
                            key="#Cities">civitate</rs> Luca; i figli di <persName><name
                                ref="Audebertus">Autberto</name></persName>; <persName>C(...)d(...)
                            de <placeName ref="#places/167">Octavo</placeName></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Raginbaldus de Fundannio">Ragimbaldo</name> de
                                <placeName ref="#places/168">Fundannio</placeName></persName>; i
                        figli di <persName><name ref="Roppaldus">Roppaldo</name></persName> beni ad
                            <placeName ref="#places/169">Ancliana</placeName>; i figli di
                                <persName><name ref="Filoardus">Filoardo</name></persName> beni in
                            <placeName ref="#places/170">Decimo</placeName> et in <placeName
                            ref="#places/171">Mozano</placeName>; <persName ref="#people/149"
                            >Cunimundo</persName> beni in <placeName ref="#places/1"
                            >Ilice</placeName> et in <placeName ref="#places/172">Flaviana seu in
                            Arcana</placeName>; il <rs key="#Other_clerics">chierico</rs>
                        <persName key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName>
                        beni della <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San
                            Pietro Somaldi</orgName>; <persName><name ref="Dodo"
                            >Toto</name></persName> e <persName><name ref="Gheroinus"
                            >Geroimo</name></persName> il <orgName key="#Monasteries"><rs
                                key="#Monasteries">monastero</rs> di Santa Maria</orgName>; il
                        figlio di <persName><name ref="Petripertus">Petriperto</name></persName>; i
                        figli di <persName><name ref="Petrus">Pietro</name></persName> beni in
                            <placeName ref="#places/190">Garfaniana</placeName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Adroaldus">Atrialdo</name></persName> beni a
                            <placeName>Asanico</placeName>; i figli di <persName><name
                                ref="Cuneradus">Corrado</name></persName> beni della <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di Santa Maria</orgName>
                        qui est da <rs key="#Clusae/gates">porta Sancti Donati</rs>; <persName><name
                                ref="Dodo">Toto</name></persName> figlio di <persName><name
                                ref="Cuneradus">Corrado</name></persName> beni a <placeName
                            ref="#places/175">Siviliano</placeName>; <persName><name ref="Aemilius"
                                >Emillo</name></persName> beni a <placeName ref="#places/178"
                            >Ito</placeName> e in altri luoghi; <persName><name ref="Willeradus"
                                >Willerado</name></persName> figlio di <persName><name ref="Petrus"
                                >Pietro</name></persName> beni a <placeName ref="#places/176"
                            >Castiliono</placeName> e in altri luoghi; <persName><name
                                ref="Robertus de Variana">Roperto</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/185">Variana</placeName></persName> beni nello stesso
                        luogo; il figlio di <persName><name ref="Albo">Albone</name></persName> beni
                        a <placeName ref="#places/186">Agello</placeName>; i figli di
                                <persName><name ref="Widelgrimus">Widalgrimo</name></persName> beni
                        a <placeName>Crete</placeName>; <persName><name ref="Adalbertus de Capelle"
                                >Adalberto</name> de <placeName ref="#places/184"
                                >Capelle</placeName></persName>; il figlio di <persName><name
                                ref="Liutfredus">Liutifrido</name></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Ardemannus">Ardimanno</name></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Rainbertus de Fugiano">Ragimperto</name> de
                                <placeName>Fugiano</placeName></persName>; il <rs key="#Priests"
                            >prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Natalis">Natale</name></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Teudemundus">Teudimundo</name></persName>; i
                        fratelli <persName><name ref="Ilpulfus">Ilpolfo</name></persName> e
                                <persName><name ref="Bertaldus">Bertaldo</name></persName>; il <rs
                            key="#Priests">prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Sicardus">Sicardo</name></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Bertaldus de Suriano">Bertaldo</name> de
                                <placeName ref="#places/188">Suriano</placeName></persName> beni a
                            <placeName ref="#places/189">Campo Cassioli</placeName>; il <rs
                            key="#Other_clerics">chierico</rs>
                        <persName key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Baldo">Baldo</name></persName>; i
                        fratelli <persName><name ref="Albo">Albone</name></persName> e
                                <persName><name ref="Andreas">Andrea</name></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Adalbertus de Mangoniani ">Adalberto</name> de
                                <placeName ref="#places/187">Mangoniani</placeName></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Rofredus">Roffridi</name></persName> la
                            <orgName key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di <placeName
                                ref="#places/165">Sexto</placeName></orgName> con le sue pertinenze;
                        i figli di <persName ref="#people/151">Adaldo</persName> la <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San
                            Terenzio</orgName> con le sue pertinenze; <persName><name
                                ref="Warnerius">Warnerio</name></persName> la <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San Michele
                            Arcangelo</orgName>; <persName><name ref="Ademarius"
                            >Ademari</name></persName>; il <rs key="#Other_clerics">chierico</rs>
                        <persName key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Giselbrandus"
                            >Ghiselprando</name></persName> pertinenze della <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San Pietro</orgName>;
                        il <rs key="#Priests">prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Ghisulfus">Ghisolfo</name></persName> il
                            <orgName key="#Monasteries"><rs key="#Monasteries">monastero</rs> di San
                            Michele Arcangelo</orgName>; <persName><name ref="Aglibertus"
                                >Agliperto</name></persName> una casa; <persName><name ref="Atto"
                                >Ato</name></persName> la <orgName key="#Churches"><rs
                                key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San Nazario</orgName>; il <rs
                            key="#Priests">prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Atto">Ato</name></persName> e il <rs
                            key="#Other_clerics">chierico</rs>
                        <persName key="#Other_clerics"><name ref="Dodo">Toto</name></persName> una
                        casa; <persName><name ref="Alamundus">Alamundo</name></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Michael">Michele</name></persName>;
                                <persName><name ref="Theudelasius de Monte Culacio"
                                >Teudilascio</name> de <placeName ref="#places/181">Monte
                                Culacio</placeName></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Anselmus de Castaneclo">Anselmo</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/182">Castaneclo</placeName></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Atto">Ato</name></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Fraolmus de Wammo">Fraolmi</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/179">Wammo</placeName></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Adalbrandus">Adalprando</name></persName>; il <rs>prete</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Angelus">Angelo</name></persName> un <rs
                            key="#Monasteries">monastero</rs>; <persName><name
                                ref="Willeramus de Vacule">Willeramo</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/180">Vacule</placeName></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Adroaldus de Placaio">Ateraldo</name> de
                                <placeName>Placaio</placeName></persName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Lambertus de Fereniana">Lamberto</name> de <placeName
                                ref="#places/163">Fereniana</placeName></persName>; <persName
                            ref="#people/147">Lamberto</persName> che fu fratello di <persName
                            ref="#people/148">Rodilando</persName>; <persName><name ref="Cunimundus"
                                >Cunimundo</name></persName>; <persName><name ref="Rainfredus"
                                >Raginfridi</name></persName> con i suoi nepotes; i <rs
                            key="#Priests">preti</rs>
                        <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Sindebertus"
                            >Sindiperto</name></persName> e <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Benedictus">Benedetto</name></persName> la <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San Lorenzo di
                                <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/166"
                            >Tempaniano</placeName></orgName>, pertinenza <orgName
                            key="#Mother_churches">Sancti Ioanni Babtista</orgName>; <persName><name
                                ref="Iohannes">Giovanni</name> de (...)</persName> la <orgName
                            key="#Churches"><rs key="#Churches">chiesa</rs> di San
                        Lorenzo</orgName>. Il vescovo chiede che costoro, i quali asseriscono di
                        avere ricevuto i suddetti beni in <rs key="#Libellus/precaria/emphyteusis"
                            >livello</rs>, si presentino e dicano pro qua causa ipsas res detinent;
                        sebbene chiamati per multus <rs key="#Assembly">placitus</rs> presencia <rs
                            key="#Missus_regis">missi inperialis</rs> seu <rs key="#Count"
                            >comitum</rs> et modo per tres civitatis presencia, costoro non si sono,
                        infatti, mai presentati in giudizio. Gli imputati, fatti cercare intus et
                        foris eodem placito, sono assenti anche in questa occasione; il vescovo
                        viene, dunque, investito per fuste dal conte di palazzo e dal marchese salva
                        querimonia dei suddetti beni, ad pars del <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/68" key="#Mother_churches"><rs
                                key="#Mother_churches">vescovato</rs> di San Martino</orgName>. Il
                        conte di palazzo e il marchese pongono sopra gli stessi beni un <rs
                            key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">banno imperiale</rs> di <rs
                            key="#Penalty">2000 mancusi d’oro</rs>; metà da versare alla <rs
                            key="#Camera_regis">camera regia</rs>, metà ad pars del vescovato.
                        L’inviato e i giudici imperiali chiedono al <rs key="#Notary #Judge">notaio
                            e giudice imperiale</rs>
                        <persName key="#Notary #Judge"><name ref="Leo">Leone</name></persName> la
                        scrittura della noticia. Sottoscrittori: <persName
                            key="#Palatine_count #Missus_regis" ref="#people/135">Amedeo</persName>
                        <rs key="#Palatine_count">comes palacii</rs>, <persName
                            key="#Marquis/duke #Count" ref="#people/137">Adalberto</persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comes</rs> et <rs key="#Marquis/duke">marchio</rs>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Iohannes">Giovanni</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Adalbertus">Adalberto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatori</rs>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Adalbertus">Adalberto</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudex domni imperatoris</rs>.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="editions">
                <p>MDL, 4/2, App. n. 55, pp. 70-72; Manaresi, n. 102, pp. 368-373;
                        <ref>http://saame.it/fonte/placiti-toscani-toscana-20/#_edn49</ref>; ChLA
                    86, n. 45, pp. 137-141.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="additional">
                <p>Tomei 2012; Tomei 2014.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="bibliography" subtype="links">
                <p/>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Fa fede l’indizione in quanto lo scrittore, come altri notai della cancelleria di
                    Lamberto, calcola l’anno d’impero partendo dal 1° gennaio. Cfr. con breve de
                    feora e breve de multis pensionibus. Sottoscrizioni autografe: il giudice
                    Giovanni, il giudice Adalberto, il giudice Adalberto.</p>
            </div>
